-- China benchmark money rate drops below 3 pct at open
-- By Pete Sweeney
-- Tue Apr 15, 2014 09:48PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, April 16 (Reuters) - China's benchmark seven-day bond repurchase rate <CN7DRP=CFXS> opened at 2.7 percent on Wednesday morning, down 73 basis points from Tuesday's close and marking the first time the rate has opened below 3 percent since mid-March.

